在2000年代后期，美国制造业从2008年[[经济大衰退|大衰退]]中复苏的速度超过了其他经济部门，<ref>{{Cite news|title=Rustbelt recovery: Against all the odds, American factories are coming back to life. Thank the rest of the world for that|url=https://www.economist.com/node/18332894|accessdate=September 21, 2011|work=The Economist|date=March 10, 2011|archive-date=2017-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170724221826/http://www.economist.com/node/18332894|dead-url=no}} [http://www.acmeind.com/wp-content/uploads/Economist_Rustbelt_Recovery_031011.pdf PDF] {{Wayback|url=http://www.acmeind.com/wp-content/uploads/Economist_Rustbelt_Recovery_031011.pdf |date=20170611024302 }}</ref>并且许多公共和私人倡议都鼓励发展替代燃料、纳米技术和其他科技。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Greening the rustbelt: In the shadow of the climate bill, the industrial Midwest begins to get ready|url=https://www.economist.com/node/14214855|accessdate=September 21, 2011|work=The Economist|date=August 13, 2009|archive-date=2018-02-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180216210318/http://www.economist.com/node/14214855|dead-url=no}}</ref>所谓的“锈带”——连同邻近的[[安大略省|加拿大]]南部[[安大略省|安大略省]]的[[金馬蹄地區|金馬蹄地區]]——仍然是世界主要的制造业地区之一。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Major Manufacturing Regions of the World|url=https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&q=cache:fnpUF-Xs3KYJ:faculty.washington.edu/beyers/Chapter7_Warf.ppt+manufacturing+regions+of+the+world&hl=en&gl=us&pid=bl&srcid=ADGEESgeUfyEVJ5-UCp5x3EGgctSVlVRoGItKLn-AVIw0gHisfIXJfVXNS0dClkwio0EWrpZ3SoH8Pfw2z0ryZ2eV8thdhyVXBYU3abQthuNuf8L4Dkj1O1DhZ22H7OWQNI_K9VdPqPX&sig=AHIEtbTNoQ3I1K5J25TpcXYenB0tMs3lIg|accessdate=September 21, 2011|author=Beyers|first=William|publisher=Department of Geography, the University of Washington|archive-date=2021-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211224173113/https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&q=cache%3AfnpUF-Xs3KYJ%3Afaculty.washington.edu%2Fbeyers%2FChapter7_Warf.ppt+manufacturing+regions+of+the+world&hl=en&gl=us&pid=bl&srcid=ADGEESgeUfyEVJ5-UCp5x3EGgctSVlVRoGItKLn-AVIw0gHisfIXJfVXNS0dClkwio0EWrpZ3SoH8Pfw2z0ryZ2eV8thdhyVXBYU3abQthuNuf8L4Dkj1O1DhZ22H7OWQNI_K9VdPqPX&sig=AHIEtbTNoQ3I1K5J25TpcXYenB0tMs3lIg|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.maderacountyedc.com/mcedc_feb2013/mfg213.pdf Rust Belt is still the heart of U.S. manufacturing]{{Dead link|date=September 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref>

=== 转型 ===
1980年代以来，总统候选人都倾注了大量的时间在锈带地区的经济问题，其中包括人口众多的[[搖擺州|搖擺州]][[宾夕法尼亚州|宾夕法尼亚州]]、[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]]和[[密歇根州|密歇根州]]。这些州对[[唐納·川普|唐纳德·特朗普]]在[[2016年美國總統選舉|2016年美国总统大选]]中获胜也至关重要，起到了决定性作用。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The revolt of the Rust Belt: place and politics in the age of anger|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/1468-4446.12328/full?hootPostID=0c84033ac0864ddb43148fcffef49385|last=Michael McQuarrie|date=2017-11-08|journal=The British Journal of Sociology|issue=S1|doi=10.1111/1468-4446.12328|doi-broken-date=2020-03-23|volume=68|pages=S120–S152|pmid=29114874|access-date=2020-05-25|archive-date=2017-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171210015601/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/1468-4446.12328/full?hootPostID=0c84033ac0864ddb43148fcffef49385|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[布鲁金斯学会|布鲁金斯学会]]2010年的一份报告回顾了锈带州的过去并展望了其未来，认为五大湖区具有巨大的转型潜力，其原因是既有的全球贸易网络、清洁能源/低碳产能、发达的创新基础设施以及高等教育网络。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Next Economy: Economic Recovery and Transformation in the Great Lakes Region|url=https://www.brookings.edu/research/the-next-economy-economic-recovery-and-transformation-in-the-great-lakes-region/|author=John C. Austin, Jennifer Bradley, and Jennifer S. Vey|date=September 27, 2010|publisher=Brookings Institution Paper|accessdate=2020-05-25|archive-date=2018-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116001246/https://www.brookings.edu/research/the-next-economy-economic-recovery-and-transformation-in-the-great-lakes-region/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

为了逆转昔日工厂带的命运，人们提出了不同的策略，包括建造赌场和会议中心、通过艺术和市区更新保留所谓的“创意阶层”、鼓励“知识型”经济的企业家精神等。最近，有分析人士认为，工业复苏可能是该地区未来复苏的实际路径。这包括通过增加一批熟练的劳动力来发展新的工业基地，重建基础设施和基础制度，建立产学研之间的合作伙伴关系以及中央、州和地方政府与企业之间的紧密合作。<ref>{{Cite web |author=Joel Kotkin, March Schill, Ryan Streeter. |title=Clues From The Past: The Midwest As An Aspirational Region |url=http://www.newgeography.com/files/MIDWEST-ASPIRATIONAL-REGION-2012.pdf |publisher=Sagamore Institute |date=February 2012 |access-date=2020-05-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200601103914/http://www.newgeography.com/files/MIDWEST-ASPIRATIONAL-REGION-2012.pdf |archive-date=2020-06-01 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

最近，锈带出现了新型的研发密集型非传统制造业，例如[[生物技术|生物技术]]、[[聚合物科學|聚合物]]行业、[[信息技术|信息技术]]和[[纳米技术|纳米技术]]。其中[[信息技术|信息技术]]尤其为锈带的复兴创造了充满希望的前景。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Silicon Rust Belt » Rethink The Rust Belt|url=http://siliconrustbelt.com/rethink-the-rust-belt/|author=Circle|first=Cheetah Interactive, Paul|publisher=|access-date=2020-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821111513/http://siliconrustbelt.com/rethink-the-rust-belt/|archive-date=2018-08-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref>最近成功案例之一是底特律飞机公司（{{Lang|en|Detroit Aircraft Corporation}}），该公司专门从事无人机系统的集成、测试和航空摄影服务。<ref>{{Cite web|title=ASX - Airspace Experience Technolgies - Detroit MI - VTOL|url=https://www.iflyasx.com/|work=ASX|accessdate=2020-05-25|archive-date=2020-06-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200613210358/https://www.iflyasx.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在匹兹堡，机器人研究中心和诸如{{Link-en|国家机器人工程中心|National Robotics Engineering Center}}和机器人研究所、Aethon Inc.、美国机器人公司、Automatika、Quantapoint、Blue Belt Technologies和Seegrid之类的公司正在创建最先进的机器人技术应用。[[阿克伦_(俄亥俄州)|阿克伦]]过去曾是“世界橡胶之都”，但在主要轮胎和橡胶制造商[[古德里奇公司|古德里奇]]、[[凡士通|凡士通]]和{{Link-en|将军轮胎|General Tire}}关闭生产线后失去了35,000个工作岗位，而现在又作为聚合物研究的中心再次在世界范围内广为人知，该地区拥有四百多间聚合物相关的制造和分销公司。之所以能够实现这一转变，部分原因是选择留下的[[固特异|固特异轮胎橡胶公司]]、[[艾克朗大學|艾克朗大學]]和市长办公室之间的合作。帮助启动了许多成功的企业创业的Akron Global Business Accelerator就位于翻新后的BF Goodrich轮胎工厂中。<ref>{{cite news|author=Sherry Karabin|url=http://www.akronlegalnews.com/editorial/7004|title=Mayor says attitude is key to Akron’s revitalization|website=The Akron Legal News|date=May 16, 2013|accessdate=2020-05-25|archive-date=2017-07-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715070514/http://www.akronlegalnews.com/editorial/7004|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

[[3D打印|增材制造或3D打印]]为制造业复兴提供了另一条有前景的道路。诸如俄亥俄州{{Link-en|比奇伍德 (俄亥俄州)|Beachwood, Ohio|比奇伍德}}的MakerGear或宾夕法尼亚州{{Link-en|北亨廷顿镇 (宾夕法尼亚州威斯特摩兰县)|North Huntingdon Township, Westmoreland County, Pennsylvania|北亨廷顿镇}}的ExOne公司这样的公司正在设计和制造使用3D成像系统的工业和消费产品。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.post-gazette.com/business/businessnews/2013/06/13/Conference-in-Pittsburgh-shows-growing-allure-of-3-D-printing/stories/201306130342|title=Conference in Pittsburgh shows growing allure of 3-D printing|author=Len Boselovic|publisher=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|date=June 13, 2013|accessdate=2020-05-25|archive-date=2017-12-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230075311/http://www.post-gazette.com/business/businessnews/2013/06/13/Conference-in-Pittsburgh-shows-growing-allure-of-3-D-printing/stories/201306130342|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2013年，总部位于伦敦的《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》杂志指出，制造业回归的趋势正在兴起，越来越多的美国公司将其生产设施从海外转移回国内。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/news/special-report/21569570-growing-number-american-companies-are-moving-their-manufacturing-back-united|title=Coming home: A growing number of American companies are moving their manufacturing back to the United States|work=The Economist|date=Jan 19, 2013|accessdate=2013-06-20|archive-date=2013-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622030754/http://www.economist.com/news/special-report/21569570-growing-number-american-companies-are-moving-their-manufacturing-back-united|dead-url=no}}</ref>锈带州最终可以从承接国际[[外判|外包]]业务的过程中受益。

也有人试图在锈带重新挖掘地产的潜力，以扭转其经济的颓势。一些开间不适合当下用途的建筑物被收购并翻新，以容纳新的商业和产业。这些商业活动表明，一度萧条的锈带正在复苏。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/business/economy/rust-belt-states-reinvent-their-abandoned-industrial-landscapes-1.3746893|title=Rust Belt states reinvent their abandoned industrial landscapes|last=Dayton|first=Stephen Starr in|last2=Ohio|website=The Irish Times|language=en|date=2019-01-05|access-date=2020-01-26|archive-date=2020-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107234522/https://www.irishtimes.com/business/economy/rust-belt-states-reinvent-their-abandoned-industrial-landscapes-1.3746893|dead-url=no}}</ref>

